---
description: Forbid single-line function and method bodies
globs: **/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# No single-line functions

A function or method whose entire body is one statement adds indirection without value. Inline the call at the invocation site instead.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — wrapper that just delegates
export function respondUpstreamUnavailable(res: Response, integration: string, message: string): void {
  res.status(httpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE).json({ error: message, integration })
}

// ✅ GOOD — call the statement directly at the call site
res.status(httpStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE).json({ error: message, integration } satisfies ApiErrorBody)
```

This applies to standalone functions, class methods, and arrow functions alike. If the abstraction is genuinely reusable and non-trivial, give it a multi-statement body (e.g. add a log line, derive a value).
